I think it's a good friendship when you...

Accept
- accept your friend the way they are
- see your friend's strengths
- see your friend's weaknesses and either have positive feeling about them or just accept them
Emotionally interconnected
- care how your friend is doing and ask regularly
- feel bad & help when your friend is having a difficult period
- feel good & congratulate when your friend is having a great time
Trust
- share & protect sensitive private information
- provide important difficult-to-communicate feedback
Believe
- believe that your friend can achieve big goals
Spend time
- enjoy spending time with your friend
